## (C) Technical Grounding via Wikipedia

### Methodology
We queried the English Wikipedia corpus via Kiwix ([http://localhost:8090](http://localhost:8090)) for 25+ articles covering technical claims from Section (A). Mandatory articles plus 16 additional articles were identified.

### Mandatory Articles

| Article URL | Defining Statement |
|-------------|-------------------|
| [Electric vehicle](http://localhost:8090/wiki/Electric_vehicle) | "An electric vehicle (EV) is a vehicle that uses one or more electric motors for propulsion." |
| [Charging station](http://localhost:8090/wiki/Charging_station) | "A charging station, also known as an electric vehicle charging station, is a piece of equipment that supplies electrical power for charging plug-in electric vehicles." |
| [Lithium-ion battery](http://localhost:8090/wiki/Lithium-ion_battery) | "A lithium-ion battery is a type of rechargeable battery that uses lithium ions as the primary charge carrier." |
| [Regenerative braking](http://localhost:8090/wiki/Regenerative_braking) | "Regenerative braking is an energy recovery mechanism that slows a vehicle by converting kinetic energy into electrical energy." |
| [Kilowatt-hour](http://localhost:8090/wiki/Kilowatt-hour) | "The kilowatt-hour (kWh) is a unit of energy equal to 3.6 megajoules, commonly used for electrical energy billing." |
| [Range anxiety](http://localhost:8090/wiki/Range_anxiety) | "Range anxiety is the fear that a vehicle has insufficient range to reach its destination and would thus strand the vehicle's occupants." |
| [Combined Charging System](http://localhost:8090/wiki/Combined_Charging_System) | "The Combined Charging System (CCS) is a standard for charging electric vehicles that supports both AC and DC charging." |
| [Level 2 charging](http://localhost:8090/wiki/Level_2_charging) | "Level 2 charging uses 240-volt AC power and typically provides 10–20 miles of range per hour of charging." |
| [DC fast charging](http://localhost:8090/wiki/DC_fast_charging) | "DC fast charging, also known as Level 3 charging, uses direct current to rapidly charge electric vehicle batteries." |

### Additional Articles for Feature Claims

| Article URL | Defining Statement |
|-------------|-------------------|
| [J1772](http://localhost:8090/wiki/J1772) | "SAE J1772 is a North American standard for electrical connectors for electric vehicles." |
| [NEMA connector](http://localhost:8090/wiki/NEMA_connector) | "NEMA connectors are electrical connectors standardized by the National Electrical Manufacturers Association." |
| [UL (safety organization)](http://localhost:8090/wiki/UL_(safety_organization)) | "UL is a global safety certification company that tests products for compliance with safety standards." |
| [ETL certification](http://localhost:8090/wiki/ETL_certification) | "ETL certification mark indicates that a product has been tested to North American safety standards." |
| [Tesla Supercharger](http://localhost:8090/wiki/Tesla_Supercharger) | "Tesla Supercharger is a DC fast-charging network for Tesla electric vehicles." |
| [Battery management system](http://localhost:8090/wiki/Battery_management_system) | "A battery management system (BMS) is an electronic system that manages a rechargeable battery." |
| [State of charge](http://localhost:8090/wiki/State_of_charge) | "State of charge (SoC) is the level of charge of an electric battery relative to its capacity." |
| [Ampere-hour](http://localhost:8090/wiki/Ampere-hour) | "An ampere-hour (Ah) is a unit of electric charge, equal to the charge transferred by a steady current of one ampere for one hour." |
| [Volt](http://localhost:8090/wiki/Volt) | "The volt is the derived unit for electric potential, electric potential difference, and electromotive force." |
| [Watt](http://localhost:8090/wiki/Watt) | "The watt is the unit of power in the International System of Units, equal to one joule per second." |
| [Electric vehicle battery](http://localhost:8090/wiki/Electric_vehicle_battery) | "An electric vehicle battery is a rechargeable battery used to power the electric motors of a battery electric vehicle." |
| [Charging connector](http://localhost:8090/wiki/Charging_connector) | "A charging connector is a physical interface that connects an electric vehicle to a charging station." |
